Was seeing the same error and debugged this a little bit. I threw in some logs into `marker/services/ollama.py` to see what the actual error response from ollama was and it was:
```json
{"error":"invalid JSON schema in format"}
```
So I printed out what format was being passed into the payload and got this result:
```python
{'type': 'object', 'properties': {'analysis': {'title': 'Analysis', 'type': 'string'}, 'correction_type': {'title': 'Correction Type', 'type': 'string'}, 'blocks': {'items': {'$ref': '#/$defs/BlockSchema'}, 'title': 'Blocks', 'type': 'array'}}, 'required': ['analysis', 'correction_type', 'blocks']}
```
I figure the issue is with the whole `'items': {'$ref': '#/$defs/BlockSchema'}` part. I threw in a schema flattener at the top of `ollama.py`:
```python
def flatten_schema(schema):
    if not isinstance(schema, dict):
        return schema

    defs = schema.pop('$defs', {})

    def resolve_refs(obj):
        if isinstance(obj, dict):
            if '$ref' in obj:
                ref_name = obj['$ref'].split('/')[-1]
                return resolve_refs(defs.get(ref_name, {}))
            else:
                return {k: resolve_refs(v) for k, v in obj.items()}
        elif isinstance(obj, list):
            return [resolve_refs(item) for item in obj]
        return obj

    return resolve_refs(schema)
```
And used it to flatten the schema before it's used:
```python
        schema = response_schema.model_json_schema()
        schema = flatten_schema(schema)
        format_schema = {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": schema["properties"],
            "required": schema["required"],
        }
```
And that seemed to fix the issue for me.

If I get a little bit of time I'll throw up a PR, but I'm not a maintainer/contributor or anything so I may not get around to it...but I hope this info helps anyone who does end up trying to fix it :)

